8 HOUSE AMENDMENT “ ” to COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to S.P. 689,
9 L.D. 1771, “An Act to Strengthen Oversight of Kennels by Changing the Licensing
10 Authority from Municipalities to the Department of Agriculture, Conservation and
11 Forestry”
12 Amend the amendment in the 2nd instructional paragraph in the 3rd line (page 1, line
13 30 in amendment) by striking out the following: "appointed"
14 Amend the amendment in the 2nd instructional paragraph in the 4th line (page 1, line
15 31 in amendment) by inserting after the following: "rule." the following: 'If the municipality
16 does not have an animal control officer, the humane agent may conduct an inspection of a
17 kennel by request as determined by the department by rule.'
18 Amend the amendment in the 5th instructional paragraph in the 4th line (page 2, line
19 11 in amendment) by inserting after the following: "application." the following: 'The
20 individual shall pay for the background check.'
21 Amend the amendment by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
22 section number to read consecutively.
23 SUMMARY
2244 This amendment amends Committee Amendment "A" to allow a humane agent to
2255 conduct an inspection of a kennel without an animal control officer, if the municipality
2266 does not have an animal control officer, as determined by the Department of Agriculture,
2277 Conservation and Forestry by rule. It removes the term "appointed" to describe an animal
2288 control officer. It also requires an individual to pay for the background check on
2299 application for licensure under the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 7, chapter 723.
